The paper deals with unsupervised domain transfer, which is a problem in machine learning and computer vision. The proposed method involves re-weighting training samples to correct for mass shift between transferred distributions, which is a technique used in many machine learning algorithms. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also mentions the use of generative adversarial networks (GANs), which are a type of neural network used in deep learning, so cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is also a possible sub-category. Lastly, the paper deals with image-to-image translation, which involves natural language processing, so cs.CL (Computation and Language) is a less likely but still possible sub-category.
